{
  "texts": [
    "(A) Diffusion-based generative models.",
    "Protein structures are represented by the distribution p(x) of atomic coordinates in three-dimensional space.",
    "During training, true atomic coordinates X 0 are progressively corrupted by Gaussian noise until reaching a normal distribution N (0, 1).",
    "At inference, the model reverses this process, iteratively denoising random noise to reconstruct a protein structure.",
    "(B) Sequence-based generative models."
  ]
}